big-o/a-big-o-intro.title: Introduction to Big O Notation
big-o/a-big-o-intro.description: "O" of "Big O" comes from “Order,” which is related to the rate of growth—for example, of time or space required to solve a given coding problem. Time complexity is used to describe the total runtime of a program. Space complexity is used to describe the total space/memory required to execute that program.
